==Digital Data == Digital data is represented by a binary number stored as a series of bits. In digital systems a bit can only has either the value 0 or 1 .
A '''bit''' can only have either value '''0''' or '''1''' which is equivalent to : '''Swith On''' is '''1''' . '''Swith Off''' is '''0''' : '''High is '''1''' . '''Low''' is '''0''' : '''Positive''' is '''1''' . '''Negative''' is '''0'''
{{BookCat}}

