==Gate turn-off thyristor (GTO)== A '''gate turn-off thyristor (GTO)''' is a special type of [[thyristor]], a high-power [[semiconductor device]]. GTOs, as opposed to normal thyristors, are fully controllable switches which can be turned on and off by their third lead, the GATE lead. : [[File:GTO.png|100px]]
==Reference== # [http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gate_turn-off_thyristor Gate_turn-off_thyristor]
